The need for speed The Run fights across America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with a routine morning shift to work.
To a certain extent, this fills everyone's ambition, but it is useless if no one wants to do anything else.
The new subtitled The Run has produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new lead with the already old Need for Speed racing series and to release a kind of game from the playable parts that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be in which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was achieved.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole pulls down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of incomprehensible idleness on the part of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught up in the adventure of which the main hero Jack has characteristic problems and to solve them starts to participate in illegal races throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on another route and the stages planned in different environments that are quite distinct from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are quite nice overcroft even though the technical level graphics is of the same type as the previous series.
Well, that's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in high snow mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition to a time in which an atypical element is added.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you must be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Next to that the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments you try to exceed the number of opponents requested (as in a classic race) then you run against the watch (classical duel with the timer) and then another duel awaits you with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police entering the game and trying to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle crossings.
It's more of an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by typing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than what you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is quite like this because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but one cannot say that it is negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you'll have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after some time.
At the difference of the driving model, the collision model is not yet in place.
We do not expect a complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you do not have, in a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it is therefore not completely good.
During tight exceedances you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your self shares in crazy volts.
Or it's in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done so that when you have broken the figure or you have come out in the setting the game will bring you back at the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you must restart the game from the beginning.
So it's more a tool, in case something doesn't happen properly, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts don't help and you have to find the solution by remembering the part of the route in question.
The big highlight of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are some turns that need to be passed in a certain way or it doesn't.
Otherwise you meet in a given place "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute late.
What upsets you are situations when you see easily passing the opponent between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you either have to stand aside and bypass them or brake them.
It doesn't matter if you go to meet him because it's "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation he always comes close to your nose.
Opponents still have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This gets the most annoying at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at all costs pass before you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you come into collision a lot of times.
We can understand that the goal of this game is to do something exciting and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And that's too bad because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn't matter if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is the car change during the races.
You need to pay attention to gasoline pumps on the routes as you can change cars there however most of the time you have enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American cylinders for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic sights on very technical pipelines for example on laced roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile, which is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This one connects online with the Autolog function which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult blows to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway train that sends you the car directly to the scrap yard.
In the writing we had a discussion for a few days as to whether someone really thought about the creation of this game or whether the authors really think we are idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is disturbing is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This is especially true of accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is the choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the most young audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game didn't have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it is not finished.
The fun is really good but prepare for mistakes to hit you in the eyes with the force of an aerodrome reflector.
Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from high schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts organized on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part to play in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the rector Vaclav Hampl", says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choeur des lycées et classes secondaryes which takes place with free entry on 17 November from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velvets" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady where the choirs of the higher schools and that of Charles University take place.
The objective of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and recall the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and develop the creative cooperation of the young.
The main organiser is the Czech Cherry Union in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from November 16 to 20 in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs act like negativists and Eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically abolished the balance between the institutions"
"I didn't expect such a hard war."
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role", is how Milena Vicenova began her presentation at the Czech Ambassador's Faculty of Law near the European Union.
When she was able to describe the different EU bodies and their relations in such a comprehensible and visible way, to the point that many speakers at Charles University's Faculty of Law could envy her, she showed how she took her motto "understandable and openly about Europe" very seriously.
Mrs Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning, the criticisms were that he is tired, that it is a round-of-leather, that he cannot fulfill any mission and I have to say that he has cut everyone's breath because he holds his role to perfection."
"He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take from Europe."
She explained the new position of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy in the context of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "What telephone number should I call?", therefore as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater legibility of the Union's policy vis-à-vis the states, such as China or India.
No one wants to forbid us our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has experienced, lives and will live in a short time.
She described the Czech Presidency two years ago as a success.
The Czechs resolved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or organized a summit for an Eastern Partnership.
She described the fall of the government as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
According to the words of the Ambassador, "the activity has beaten its full" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to resolve itself now.
We must also approve the new septimal budget of the Union, which is becoming very complicated because of the current economic situation.
As it seems that the budget will be thin and for savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be solved in the context of future negotiations.
Madam Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
"I really don't like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that no one understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas that are differently large or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky."
It wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador the Czechs have the reputation of being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
Furthermore, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
According to her, the fault results from several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a letter of motivation and weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech Presidency, she then stressed the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Polish, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me: 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?" and he is not at all happy."
According to Mrs Vicenova, in the near future, tough new fiscal policy rules are waiting for the Member States.
It is the concept of a two-speed Europe, if not a multi-speed one, that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
"We have countries in the euro area and others outside the area."
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the enhanced cooperation institute".
In the first place it was said that the countries that want to cooperate with each other and those that do not want to remain in their corner."
"There will be many such institutes and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," says Vicenova.
From this point of view, it also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all issues having an impact on the EU should be discussed between all EU members and not just the members of the Eurozone.
History of a brand:
Innovative IBM begins the second century of its existence
If someone were to look for the word that expresses the IBM strategy as closely as possible, the closest would be "long-term".
For a large audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The basis of this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first chief, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left the slogan that many global problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE'!" became the imprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
It was the foundation of Watson's carefully crafted corporate culture.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it always remained faithful to its basic values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more"for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to take care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - the people of IBM were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacations, an insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and conmercials.
In the same way IBM has a system of relationships with the well-developed customer.
The company was at first brilliant in the discovery of talents- as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and thus could have the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman- Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been working at IBM for 30 years and currently holds the position of Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM over the past few years has been doing so-called jamy, online brainstorming from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
No wonder he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
